    "attributes": {
        "action": "Review how long prostitution related convictions stay on criminal records",
        "additional_details": "We are calling for a review of these time limits.",
        "background": "Current disclosure periods can last up to 100 years from the date of conviction, meaning offences can follow people for life and make it hard to find work or change careers. We believe that people who have left or are trying to leave the sex trade shouldn\u2019t be held back for life by old convictions.",
